This paper deals with improving the performance of TLS connections, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper proposes a new TLS extension, which involves designing and implementing software, making it relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the potential energy savings from using the proposed extension, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY).
